I chose Canva because it has a large library of free templates and icon packs that made it easy to translate text-heavy concepts into visual, scannable content. 
The most challenging part was fitting three topics into a single page without making it look cluttered.
I had to remove a fourth section on email etiquette and replace it with a simple iconographic checklist. 
The most interesting discovery was that Canva's "Brand Kit" feature — even on the free plan — lets you lock your colour palette, which kept the whole design consistent.
One thing I would do differently is use a slightly larger font for mobile viewers, since the infographic is meant to be shared in WhatsApp groups.
